    <title>Noetherianity for infinite-dimensional toric varieties</title>
    <summary>  We prove that many families of toric ideals stabilize up to symmetry. Our
results imply Hillar-Sullivant's Independent Set Theorem and settle
afformatively questions in work by Aschenbrenner-Hillar, Hillar-Sullivant, and
Hillar-Martin del Campo. Our approach involves splitting an equivariant
monomial map into a part for which we have an explicit degree bound of the
kernel, and a part for which we can prove that the source, a so-called matching
monoid, is equivariantly Noetherian.
</summary>
